  "text": "Ankles were decalcified and embedded in paraffin and sections of 6 μm were performed and stained with hematoxylin-eosin and safranin (HES). The histological features of cartilage, bone and periarticular soft tissue were evaluated in a blind fashion by using the score of Kinne et al. [CITATION_1] . According to this score, the degree of inflammatory infiltration is scored from 0 to 3 where 0 = no infiltration, 1 = slight infiltration, 2 = moderate infiltration and 3 = severe infiltration. The degree of bone and cartilage destruction is scored from 0 to 4, where 0 = no erosion of cartilage or bone, 1 = unequivocal erosion ≤ 10% of cartilage or bone trabeculae, 2 = erosions ≤ 50% 3 = erosions from 50 to 90% and 4 = erosions > 90%. The maximum score per rat is 7.",
